p: \rHello! I'm Professor Sylvan, I'm the Professor in this town.
\rI suppose you want to start your Pokemon adventure?
\rMost of the other kids in the neighborhood have already gotten their Eevee from me and headed north to the Trainer School in Midna Town.
\rYou'll have to wait a little bit, though. The town is busy preparing for the Augur's arrival, and so am I.
\rSo, you've chosen to take the Eevee I offer to all trainers-to-be?\f[133]
\bI trust you.\nIf you think not choosing one of those Pokemon is the best idea, I'll choose Eevee too.
\bI trust you.\nIf you think not choosing one of those Delta Pokemon is the best idea, I'll choose Eevee too.
\bHey \pn...\nBefore we go out into the Shade Forest, how about a battle?\nIt'll be the perfect time to test out our new Pokemon!
\bWow, you're a great battler!\nDo you think maybe you could take on a Gym someday?
\bWow, I won!\nMaybe I could even take on a Gym someday!

Alright, \pn.
Here's the deal.
I'm going to head north into Shade Forest.
At the northern end of the forest is a really large cave, and in the middle of that cave is
the Rare Stone we're looking for.\nI'll meet you there, OK?
\r\pn, can I talk to you for a moment?
\rDamian rushed off before I could give him one, but I'd like you to have this.
\rThis is the Pokedex, short for Pokemon Index.\nIt is a data collection of all Pokemon that I give to trainers.\nIf you see a Pokemon, it will be registered in the
Pokedex.\nIf you catch one, the Pokedex will be full of data regarding that Pokemon!
\rAnyways, now that you've gotten that, you should be all set to go on your adventure.
\rHead up north to Telnor Cave, deep in the forest. Be careful, and good luck!

\rSo how are your Pokemon coming along?
\rGood luck on your adventure- and remember what I said!
\rI still can't believe you beat Reukra and the Elite Four, \pn.
\rI'd love to battle you, actually. I'd like to see how I stand up against ya.
\rThat was fantastic! I'd like to reward you for that.
\rYou see... I've really done all the research I can do on this Pokemon.
\rI'd like you to take care of it. I feel like you'd be the best caretaker possible for it.
\rAs for what it is... well, isn't it obvious?
\rIt's the third Delta Pokemon! The one that Reukra left, that neither you nor Damian took.
\rI think you'll be able to take care of it better than I can.
\rI think you'll be able to take care of it better than I can.
\rI think you'll be able to take care of it better than I can.
\rI still can't believe you beat Reukra and the Elite Four, \pn.
\rI'd love to battle you, actually. I'd like to see how I stand up against ya.
\rThat was fantastic! I'd like to reward you for that.
\rYou see... I've really done all the research I can do on these Delta Pokemon.
\rI'd like you to take care of all of them. I feel like you'd be the best caretaker possible for it.
\rHave you come to check up on how your Pokedex is faring?
\rIf you're curious about how many there are... there are all the normal, expected Pokemon.
\rThen, there's every Delta Pokemon from Delta Bulbasaur onwards.
\rDon't worry about most of those ones in between. I won't judge your Pokedex based off that.
\rWould you like me to check how many you have?
\rHere, take this, as a token of my appreciation. You've certainly earned it.
\rAlso, also! Have this fancy certificate commemorating your accomplishment!
\rNormally I'd send this to your house for safekeeping but... do you actually have a house?
\rYeah, I didn't think so. Do you have somewhere else in mind where I can send this?
\rThe first Augur's old headquarters? Okay! Be sure to be on the lookout for it!
\rYou won't believe this, but I forgot to give you another reward for completing the National Dex!
\rHere, a shiny new certificate for your hard work!
\rNormally I'd send this to your house for safekeeping but... do you actually have a house?

\rThe first Augur's old headquarters? Okay! Be sure to be on the lookout for it!
\rIt's incredible that you've caught every Pokemon.

\bListen, Professor. We just can't afford to keep them.
\bYou have a bunch of Eevee, anyway!\nIt's not like they would be a burden to you or anything.
\rIt's not that I can't, Reukra.\nIt's just that these aren't the kind of Pokemon I can give away to trainers.\nNobody's going to want them.
\bThat may be, but it'd be better if they stayed with you than with me.
\bI'm Damian, and this is \pn...\nWe're here to get a Pokemon so we can go into the forest safely.
\bSylvan, if you don't take these Pokemon, I'll release them.\nCan't you just give them to these kids?
\rOh, just put them on the table.
\rSo you two are in need of a Pokemon?
\rThat man that was in here just now, he was one of my colleagues in university.
\rHe's a smart man, and a great scientist.
\rHe's also the leader of the Cult of Perfection.
\rBut listen, that's not important right now.
\rTell me, Damian, \pn.\nHave you ever heard of something called "Delta Species"?
\rDelta Pokemon are based on a phenomenon in the Holon Region, far away.
\rThey're Pokemon that have different DNA than normal Pokemon.
\rSimply put, they're typed differently than normal.\nAn example would be an Electric-type Dragonite, or a Water-type Porygon.
\rThese Pokemon on the table now are Deltas.
\rI'm not sure what type they are, but they seem to look like Bulbasaur, Charmander, and Squirtle.
\rThey're scientific marvels. I would love to keep one to study.
\rNow! Normally, I would give you an Eevee as a Pokemon to start you off on your journey.
\rHowever, it seems there are three more options for

\b\pn, I don't know what to do.\nDelta Species seem interesting, but I'd almost rather have a regular Pokemon.\nI'll follow your lead on this one.
\bNo other Trainer would want them, and we can't keep them any longer.
\bAll I want is for you to take them.\nYou already keep a bunch of Eevee as is, surely these three won't be a bother?
\r...why do you care about them?\nI know what you've done.
\bIt's true, I'm merciless.\nI've done some awful things.\nBut there's no reason for these Pokemon to die.
